node.text:
Actress @Efira_Virginie wore a #DiorCouture white silk chiffon draped dress by @MariaGraziaChiuri to attend the Dior x @VogueParis dinner held during the 74th @FestivaldeCannes. Swipe to see other #StarsinDior at the event - from @SandrineKiberlain and jury member @MGyllenhaal to @MelanieThierry, @GadElmaleh and @JeanneDamas - talk about their experience at the famous film festival.
#DiorCannes
© Photo: @Pierre__Mouton
Video : @Dnl.Darmon

node.title: Cannes Glamour at the Dior x Vogue Paris Dinner

The book 'Threads of Life: A History of the World Through the Eye of a Needle' proved a starting point for @MariaGraziaChiuri spark for the #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2021-2022 collection. And here its author @SewingMatters discusses the overlooked importance of sewing as a millennia-old form of visual communication, a repository for ideas of identity and place, and a means of connecting people and of sharing ideas around the world. 
© Clare Hunter is a community textile artist, curator & author based in Scotland. Threads of Life is published by Sceptre, Hodder & Stoughton (UK), Abrams Press (US), Bollati Boringhieri (Italy) & Uitgeverij Balans (Amsterdam).

node.title: Reclaiming the outsized role of sewing

Uncover the awesome effort required to realize the 340m2 of embroideries that lined the show space for the unveiling of the #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2021-2022 collection by @MariaGraziaChiuri. The motifs of artist Eva Jospin's work, 'Chambre de Soie', were divided into panels and interpreted as free-flowing embroideries involving 150 different kinds of stitches and techniques, and undertaken by 300 artisans at the @Chanakya.School in Mumbai, India. Founded in 2017 by the @Chanakya.In ateliers, the school preserves exceptional techniques and empowers women in local communities by training them as master craftspeople, in India a role traditionally reserved for men. This collection is thus a celebration of the transmission and richness of savoir-faire, a collective work glorifying the borderless beauty of craft. 
© Film by @MelindaTriana

Now discover the fascinating history of Rome's opulent art-filled Palazzo Colonna, its noble family and the famous figures with which it has been associated over the centuries.
© Film by Edoardo Winspeare

© Film by @MelindaTriana
Photo: Sophie Carre

A fundamental element of #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2021-2022 for @MariaGraziaChiuri who sought textiles with natural tones and a sense of texture and tactility, tweeds were specially developed for the collection by @Lanificio_Luigi_Colombo in Italy. Some of them were used for tailoring composed of patchworks of curving pattern pieces, while, on the flipside, feathers were also employed to recreate the same speckled effect.
#DiorSavoirFaire

THE NEW JARDIN DIOR DE LA ROSE
In 2021, near Granville, the new Jardin Dior de la Rose is becoming a garden of transmission and pioneering innovation. Building on years of organic cultivation principles, it goes beyond and commits to develop the first regenerative cosmetic rose cultivation.
•
#BeautyAsALegacy #DiorBeauty #DiorSkincare #JardinDiorDeLaRose @diorbeauty

node.text:
Warm autumnal hues define this unique 'Dior Grand Soir Jardin de Nuit' watch, glowing with a tiger's eye bezel cut from a single slice and featuring a dark dial over which spills a naturalistic cascade of foliage in three golds, sapphires, garnets, scarab marquetry, diamonds and sapphires. The subtle finesse of a quartz movement at 12 o'clock contrasts with the preciousness of the case glittering with snow-set, brilliant-cut diamonds.
© @PhilippeFragniere

node.text:
Discover the delicacy of the #DiorSavoirFaire that goes into this #DiorHorlogerie collection of unique 'Dior Grand Soir Jardin de Nuit' quartz-movement watches, conjuring up the mysterious beauty of an enchanted garden after dark. Monsieur Dior's passion for plants is conveyed in the way the delicate cascades and and sproutings of foliage and flowers are crafted in a mixture of tiny precious stones, golds and platinum, with each dial surrounded by a hardstone bezel and held in a case of sparkling snow-set diamonds. 
© @PolBaril

node.text:
Drawing inspiration from Monsieur Dior's love of nature, particularly a fondness for fauna, 'Dior Grand Bal Parure Tropicale' watches are illuminated with vibrant colors that recall a bird-of-paradise. These tropical tones are created on each utterly unique piece through exceptional examples of elaborate #DiorSavoirFaire that recall plumage in their placement and give a sense of a bird in flight. Featuring a 'Dior Inversé 11 1/2 caliber' automatic movement and transparent back, the rotor can be seen on the dial where it is surrounded by the intricately painterly mixture of marquise-cut stones and scarab elytra marquetry, all framed by a bezel and case in baguette-cut or snow-set, brilliant-cut diamonds.
#DiorHorlogerie
© @PolBaril

node.text:
Get an intimate insight into the #DiorSavoirFaire behind the two newly introduced, quartz-movement 'Dior Grand Soir Aquarelle' watches. Evoking the delicate hues of watercolor, these rose gold cases with snow-set diamond bezels feature softly painted bracelets and dials, the latter like abstracted petals enhanced by the placement of gold flowers with sapphire and tinted glass touches. Each style comes in a limited edition of 18.
#DiorHorlogerie 
© @PolBaril
